Walmart Tech Mod Transportation Project – Summary  {Wal-Mart stores}

Participated in the migration of transportation applications from Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) to Ubuntu as part of Walmart’s internal cloud modernization effort.

Worked with Linux and Java technology stack, focusing on ensuring environment-specific configurations and secure file transfers between systems via SFTP.

Tested and validated JAR/WAR components to ensure compatibility with both RHEL and Ubuntu environments.

Used One-Ops for provisioning cloud environments, managing build deployments, and handling production change requests in a controlled way.

Developed and maintained configuration scripts, automated health checks, and environment monitoring tools using Java and control tower automation frameworks.

Assisted in post-migration validation, including sign-off documentation and production readiness checks. Collaborated closely with cross-functional teams to monitor applications post-migration, troubleshoot issues
